text.section:
"Owner" means:
In the case of a deposit, a depositor or a person entitled to receive the funds as reflected on the records of the bank or financial organization;
In the case of a trust, a beneficiary;
In the case of other choses in action, a creditor, claimant, or payee;
In the case of abandoned property in federal custody, the person who is defined as the owner by any applicable federal law; or
Any person who has a legal or equitable interest in property subject to this title, or the legal representative of that person.

"Personal property" does not include:
A gift certificate;
Credits in connection with the sale of consumer goods to a wholesaler or retailer in the ordinary course of business;
Outstanding checks or credits issued to vendors or commercial customers in the ordinary course of business, other than property described in § 17-301(a) of this title held by a banking organization or financial organization;
Credit balances in vendor or commercial customer accounts that occur in the ordinary course of business, other than property described in § 17-301(a) of this title held by a banking organization or financial organization; or
Purchase price rebates issued to customers in the ordinary course of business.
